title: ALS Road Race Series

address.street: Rock Creek Park, Lake Perry, Kansas

description:
2015 A.L.S. Road Race Series
Permit 2015-383
Road Race Series Dedicated to A.L.S.
Sunday, March 1, 8, and 15 2015 
Rock Creek Park, Perry Kansas
Co-sponsored by the Lanterne Rouge Racing Team and Big D Cycling.
Net Proceeds from this series will be donated to the Bruce Edwards Dream Fund to defeat A.L.S..
Junior Entry Fees are sponsored by the Keen Wealth Advisors.
course:
Course is a paved 5 mile loop with an uphill finish.
Course is NOT closed but corners will be supervised.
Course video available at www.lanternerougekansas.com
registration: Registration can be made on line at USA Cycling.  Day of Race registration will have $15.00 late fee attached to the pre registration fee.  No handwritten, illegible, 2015 Release Forms will be accepted.  On line "fill in the blank" release forms are available at USA Cycling.org and www.lanternerougekansas.com.  Anyone pre registering online for the entire series will receive a $15.00 discount..  If inclement weather and/or  a bonified emergency(determined by Race Director) occurs then those affected participant(s) will receive a refund via USA Cycling process. You may enter all three events and you will receive a $15.00 total saving. Registration opens at 9:15am and closes at 9:45am and then 45 minutes prior to each event and for a period of 30 minutes thus closing 15 minutes before each race.
notes:
Prizes will be A.L.S. Engraved Medals as listed below for their specific series winners.  These medals are engraved with the event, date, and rider's name.  The series winners in the cash payout will be as follows:
M Cat 1-2-3 and Women Cat 1-2-3 - 8 places
$200 - $160 - $130 - $110 - $90 - $70 - $50 - $35
M Cat 3 - 4 - 8 places
$170 - $140 - $120 -  $95 - $80 - $65 - $45 - $35
Point Scale is as follows:
1st - 10 points, 2nd - 8 points, 3rd - 7 points, 4th - 6 points, 5th - 5 points, 6th - 4 points, 7th - 3 points, 8th - 2 points - Participation Points for all races but DNS - 1 point.
Ties for monetary rewards will be broken by adding the two places together and dividing it equally.  Ties in the medals category will not be broken, each recipient will receive an engraved medal.  King/Queen of the Mountain will on the first lap only for the following Categories:  M&F Masters, F Category 4, M Category 5, Junior M&F 14 -18 AND 9-13.  Scoring will be as follows:  1st 5 points, 2nd 3 points, 3rd 2 points, and 4th 1 Point.  These points will NOT count towards the series winner.
directions: The course is approximately 4.5 miles northwest of Perry, Kansas.  From Topeka take Highway 24 east to Thompsonville Road.  Go North and follow the signs to the race headquarters located in Rock Creek Park.  From Lawrence take highway 24 west to Thompsonville Road, and follow the signs to the race headquarters.

title: Sunflower State Games Team Time Trial

course: video, course map, and elevation located at www.lanternerougekansas.com
registration:

title: Kansas Fat Tire Festival
description: XC race on rugged rolling terrain.  The course is a single loop that meanders through Lake Wilson State Park. Extremely challenging rocky sections with punchy climbs descents and drops.  Trail skirts edgy bluffs with beautiful views but keep your eyes on the trail.  You don't want to get wet.
course: The course offers excellent viewing for your fans if they are willing to travel the park road to watch your progress.
registration: Register on line at USA Cycling or at the event on the day of the race.
notes:
Elite Mens payout 1st,$1000,2nd$400,3rd$300,4th$200,5th$100
Cat 1 Men Payout 
1st$200,2nd$125,3rd$75
Pro/Cat1 Women Payout
1st$500,2nd$200,3rd$100
All other classes win righteous prizes
directions: From I-70 go north on HWY232 (mile marker206),proceed 5 Miles to State Park turn in, turn West go across Big Bridge, Turn right on your first opportunity and follow park road to Switchgrass Campground.  Sign in and ride.

title: Sunflower State Games Mountain Biking Race
Tour de Trees
description: Tour de Trees is a recreational bike ride from Johnson's Garden Center, 2707 W. 13th.  We'll leave the store Sunday, October 18th at 10:00 AM.  We'll follow the bike path along the Arkansas river continuing on both paved and gravel roads to the Bartlett Arboretum.  We'll enjoy the 2nd Annual Ecofest and lunch at the Arb.  With 2 SAG stops along the way, everybody will have a great ride.
